## Vercel Speed Insights Installation Complete

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for the Next.js project.

### Changes Made:

**1. Package Installation:**
- Installed `@vercel/speed-insights` package (v1.1.0)
- Updated `package.json` to include the new dependency
- Updated `package-lock.json` with the resolved dependency tree

**2. Configuration:**
- Modified `app/layout.tsx` to integrate Speed Insights
- Added import: `import { SpeedInsights } from "@vercel/speed-insights/next";`
- Added `<SpeedInsights />` component inside the `<body>` tag

**3. Implementation Details:**
- Followed the latest official Vercel documentation for Next.js (v13.5+)
- The SpeedInsights component is placed at the end of the body element
- This allows Vercel to track Core Web Vitals metrics including:
  - Largest Contentful Paint (LCP)
  - First Input Delay (FID)
  - Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS)
  - Time to First Byte (TTFB)

**4. Verification:**
- Build completed successfully without errors
- Linter passed with no issues
- No breaking changes to existing functionality
- All build artifacts properly ignored by git

### Files Modified:
- `app/layout.tsx` - Added SpeedInsights import and component
- `package.json` - Added @vercel/speed-insights dependency
- `package-lock.json` - Updated with new dependency tree

### Next Steps:
After deployment to Vercel, Speed Insights data will be available in the Vercel dashboard under the "Speed Insights" section. The metrics will populate once the site receives user traffic.

### Framework Details:
- Framework: Next.js 16.2.4
- Package Manager: npm
- Integration Type: Next.js App Router (app directory)
